I don't see any difference from my old Animation Desk except that I paid more money to have this one too. It seems to take a little less space than the original I own. The only thing really missing is a clear identification of framed drawing space, but the attempt of emulating a traditional animator's workspace w/o the mess of spilled ink is something I think has been done very well. The digital benefits of art, like specifying exact colors through hex or extracting a palette are not here.

I'm an associate at Walmart but my passion is Computer animation so I was looking for an app that I could use for basic animation projects on both my iPad and Samsung galaxy tablet so I searched and found this one it works well and I like the old fashion appearance of the interface. If you are looking for an app to use for basic animating I highly recommended animation desk.

content: After putting up with Apple's silly excuses for styluses for a long time, I decided to join the ANDROID community in search of a better drawing experience... Unfortunately what I gained in awesome stylus control I seem to have lost in App advancement.  The current Animation Desk for iOS has a lasso tool and a copy paste stamp tool.  This is not the only app which lags behind.  For some reason many other drawing apps in Android lag far behind their iOS counterpart yet cost the same. Please get this app updated with at least the lasso and copy tools.  It really makes a difference.  Thanks
